net.truelicense.api

Interface ConsumerLicenseManagerBuilder

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Builder<ConsumerLicenseManager>, Injection<ConsumerLicenseManagerBuilder>, LicenseManagerBuilder<ConsumerLicenseManagerBuilder>

    public interface ConsumerLicenseManagerBuilder
extends Builder<ConsumerLicenseManager>, Injection<ConsumerLicenseManagerBuilder>, LicenseManagerBuilder<ConsumerLicenseManagerBuilder>
    A builder for consumer license managers. Call its Builder.build() method to obtain the configured license consumer manager.

    Clients should not implement this interface because it's subject to expansion in future minor version updates.

    Author:
    Christian Schlichtherle

    • Method Detail

      • ftpDays

        ConsumerLicenseManagerBuilder ftpDays(int ftpDays)
        Sets the free trial period (FTP) in days (the 24 hour equivalent). If this is zero, then no FTP is configured. Otherwise, the key store needs to have a password configured for the private key entry and a parent consumer license manager needs to be configured for the regular license keys.
        Returns:
        this.

      • parent

        ConsumerLicenseManagerBuilder parent()
        Returns a builder for the parent consumer license manager. Call its Injection.inject() method to build and inject the configured parent consumer license manager into this builder and return it.

        A parent consumer license manager is required to configure a non-zero free trial period (FTP). The parent consumer license manager will be tried first whenever a life cycle management method is executed, e.g. when verifying a license key.

        See Also:
        parent(ConsumerLicenseManager)

      • parent

        ConsumerLicenseManagerBuilder parent(ConsumerLicenseManager parent)
        Sets the parent consumer license manager. A parent consumer license manager is required to configure a non-zero free trial period (FTP). The parent consumer license manager will be tried first whenever a life cycle management method is executed, e.g. when verifying a license key.
        Returns:
        this.

      • storeIn

        ConsumerLicenseManagerBuilder storeIn(Store store)
        Store the license key in the given store. If a non-zero free trial period (FTP) is configured, then the store will be used for the auto-generated FTP license key and MUST BE KEPT SECRET!
        Returns:
        this.
